The paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for the reconstruction and visualization of 3D/4D organ models from single-view medical images. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image processing and machine learning (ML) techniques for the deep neural network. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of informative latent descriptors extracted from input 2D images, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with the generation of high-fidelity manifold meshes, which involves the use of geometric modeling and computer graphics techniques, making cs.GR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential use of the proposed method in real-time image-guided radiation therapy (IGRT), which involves the use of multimedia (MM) techniques for real-time visualization.
